@node Introduction "Introduction"
                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}
                                ==============


A big Lack of the AmigaOS-Workbench is the trashcan-system.
It simply moves files in a specific directory of a volume and adds a new
menuentry for this specific directories.
A volume-independed trashcan isn't existing as long as many features that
are important for a efficient usage.

In the Aminet there are multiple programms, which create one appicon on
the workbench and so combine the multiple volumes.
Every programm has its superior feature but no one has the really important
features combinded. And there are a lot of important features I never
found in any of this programms.

So I decided to write a new one with all this features.
And this are the highlights:

  - One appicon for all volumes on the workbench.
  - Fontsensitive and appealing GUI.
  - Access to a global trashcan with the contents of all trashcan-directories
    on all volumes.
  - Ability to access a single trashcan-directory on a volume.
  - Automatically delete files that are older than a specific amount of days.
    You can use the trashcan for the backups of your programms (like GoldED,
    PageStream,...). You will always have access to your older documents and
    you can be sure that they will be deleted if they are too old.
  - Ability to start an user-defined AmigaDOS-Command for every volume (to
    eject your ZIP-Disks for example).
  - CLI-/Shell-command @{" GlobalTrashClient " link Client} can be used to direct GlobalTrash,
    so using the features from other programms (like DirectoryOpus or Tool-
    manger) is possible.
  - Different requesters with various options for interaction.
  - Progress-bar.

  - Correct processing of the same filenames in the same trashcan-directory
    (no overwriting of existent files in a trashcan directory).
  - Ability to restore a file in its original path with its original filename.
  - GUI shows a file-tree for directories.
    Ability to browse in this tree and to process (restore, delete) files from
    within this tree.
  - Recognition of files which are not moved by GlobalTrash into the trashcan
    directory (without the origin); for example a backup-file from GoldED.
  - Ability to restore files over multiple volumes.
  - Correct processing of the iconfiles (#?.info).
  - and many many more.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements"
                                 @{b}Requirements@{ub}
                                ==============


This program needs at least:

  - A 68k-computer with AmigaOS (Amiga© or Draco©).
  - AmigaOS 3.0 or greater.
  - 80-100KByte free RAM.
  - 'Copy' in the current path (normally 'C:'; for the restore-function over
    multiple volumes - this will be changed in a future version.)
  - Volumes with trashcan-directories (of course).
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"
                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}
                                ==============


You can easily install GlobalTrash by using the installerskript.
This skript does the following:

  - Copy the main program (with its icon) to 'SYS:WBStartup/' ('AVERAGE' and
    'EXPERT' asks for the path). The right version for your processor is
    choosen (with 'EXPERT' you can change which one is used.)
  - Copy the preferences program (with its icon) to 'SYS:Prefs/' ('AVERAGE' and
    'EXPERT' ask for the path.)
  - Copy the iconfiles to 'ENVARC:sys/' and 'ENV:sys/' (you can skip this
    by choosing 'EXPERT').
  - Copy the needed catalog files to 'LOCALE:catalogs/' (you can select
    them with 'EXPERT').
  - Copy the documentation to 'SYS:' ('AVERAGE' and 'EXPERT' ask for the
    path.)

The installation 'by hand' should also be very simple:

  - Copy the main file 'GlobalTrash' together with its icon into the
    directory 'SYS:WBStartup' (to start the program automatically
    after each boot-up.)
  - Copy the preferences 'GlobalTrashPrefs' together with its icon into
    the directory 'SYS:Prefs' (if you choose another location be sure to
    change the corresponding tooltype of GlobalTrash!)
  - If you want any other language than english, copy the catalog
    to 'LOCALE:catalogs' or 'PROGDIR:catalogs' along with the directory
    of the selected language.
  - Copy the contents of 'ENVARC/sys' to 'ENVARC:sys' (icon files).

  - Copy the documentation.
  - Start the program.
@endnode

@node Usage "Benutzung"
                                    @{b}Usage@{ub}
                                   =======


GlobalTrash is simple to use:

  You can drop one or more files over the GlobalTrash-appicon on the workbench.
  These files will be moved to the trashcan directory on the belonging volume
  or (if there isn't any trashcan directory on this volume) the files will be
  deleted immediately.
  Before performing any delete-action the programm will be asked if it should
  delete this file really (you can deactivate this in the @{" Preferences " link PrefWindow}).


Every other function GlobalTrash offers can be started in the @{" Mainwindow " link MainWindow}.
You can open this window with a doubleclick on the appicon, start GlobalTrash
again, press the GlobalTrash-hotkey (default: '@{b}alt g@{ub}') or open the window
with the use of 'Exchange'.

An entry in the Tools-menu of the workbench is also created. This entry
behaves identically as the appicon (choosing opens the @{" Mainwindow " link MainWindow}
or - if icons are choosen - they will be processed).

Further, you can read more about the @{" progress-bar " link ProgressBar}, the different
@{" requesters " link Requester} GlobalTrash uses for interaction and the @{" GlobalTrashClient " link Client}-
program used for external control of GlobalTrash.
@endnode

@node MainWindow "The Mainwindow"
                                @{b}The Mainwindow@{ub}
                               ================


The Main window allows the access of all the other functions (except the
delete over the appicon) the program offers. It is the central workplace of
this trashcan-system.

Apart from the @{" menu entries " link MainMenues} it looks like the following:

   --------------------------------------------------------------------
  | GlobalTrash X.XX © Oliver Blumert 1997/98                          |
   --------------------------------------------------------------------
  |                                                                    |
  |                        -----------------------------------------   |
  |  Current trashcan     |       'Global' or single volumes        |  |
  |                        -----------------------------------------   |
  |                                                                    |
  |   -------------------- ------ ----------- ----------------------   |
  |  | Name               | Size | Time Left | Origin               |  |
  |   -------------------- ------ ----------- ----------------------   |
  |  |                                                              |  |
  |  | This listview shows the filenames, the belonging filesize    |  |
  |  | (with the size of the iconfile included), the time to delete |  |
  |  | the file automatically and the original path and filename    |  |
  |  | (if unknown: the volumename e.g. 'Work:').                   |  |
  |  |                                                              |  |
  |   --------------------------------------------------------------   |
  |                                                                    |
  |   ---------------------  | Trashcan:                            |  |
  |  |       Undelete      | |   (Status-display current trashcan)  |  |
  |   ---------------------  |                                      |  |
  |  |    Undelete as...   | | Datenträger:                         |  |
  |   ---------------------  |   (Status-display current volume)    |  |
  |  |        Delete       |                                           |
  |   ---------------------   --------------------    --------------   |
  |  |         View        | |  Empty this trash  |  |    Hide      |  |
  |   ---------------------   --------------------    --------------   |
  |                                                                    |
  |--------------------------------------------------------------------|
  |                                                                | X |
   --------------------------------------------------------------------

With the gadget @{b}current trashcan@{ub} you can choose to which trashcan on which
volume the files displayed in the listview below are from. You can choose
each volume separately or the 'Global'-entry. The last one means that all files in
each trashcan directory on each volume are displayed, sorted by name in the
listview. If you select a specific volume then the displayed list is (also
sorted by name) the contents of the trashcan directory on this specific volume.
This choice also has an effect on the operation after selecting the
@{b}Empty this trash@{ub}-gadget (more below).

The gadgets on the left side invoke one of the following actions and may be
used alternativelly to the double-click:

  - @{u}Undelete:@{uu}    Move the files to their origin (it restores them).
                 If the origin is unknown then this action has the same meaning
                 as the @{b}Undelete as@{ub}-command.
                 Missing directories in the path are created automatically.
  - @{u}Undelete as:@{uu} Open a filerequester for each file. You can alter the path and
                 filename in order to restore the file in a path and with a name
                 of your choice. If the origin is known, then this is the
                 defaultname in this requester (which you can alter).
  - @{u}Delete:@{uu}      Delete the selected files.
  - @{u}View:@{uu}        Display the selected files; it is differed after the filetype.
                 @{b}This option will be selectable with version 1.4 of GlobalTrash!@{ub}

By selecting the gadget @{b}Empty this trash@{ub} you will delete the contents of the
trashcan displayed above.
If the selected trashcan is the 'Global' one, then you will delete all files
in each trashcan directory on each volume.

The gadget @{b}Hide@{ub} will close the mainwindow and GlobalTrash will stay behind
and wait for any action.


The center of the GlobalTrash-GUI is the @{b}listview@{ub}-Gadget.
This gadget displays a list of files which represants the contents of the
selected volume or all volumes in the system.
Each entry has multiple sections:

  - @{u}Name:@{uu}      Stands for the filename in the trashcan directory.
               In front of this name is an image displayed which represents
               the type of this file (if this is known by the program).
               If the entry stands for a directory, then in front of this image
               will by displayed another image (an arrow). With this arrow, you
               can open or close the directory. If a directory is open, then
               this will be displayed as a kind of directory-tree (which
               you can fold or unfold). You can apply every action on these
               files as on every other file (undelete or delete).
  - @{u}Size:@{uu}      Stands for the file size inclusive of the associated
               icon file ('.info') - if there is any.
  - @{u}Time left:@{uu} Stands for the amount of days this file will be left in the
               trashcan directory before it will be automatically deleted.
               If this feature is deactivated, then @{b}«off»@{ub} will be displayed.
  - @{u}Origin:@{uu}    Stands for the original path and filename of this file.
               If you can read only a volume name (e.g. 'Work:') then the
               origin is unknown to GlobalTrash (e.g., another program moved
               the file into the trashcan directory) and the @{b}Undelete@{ub}-command
               has the same effect as the @{b}Undelete as@{ub}-command.

In this listview you can select or deselect multiple files. All you have to do
is to press the left mousebutten and move it up or down without releasing it.
No need to hold down the shift key!
A second way is to select each file by clicking once on each entry.
A double-click performs the action choosen by the @{b}current command@{ub}-gadget
(inclusive of the entry you double-clicked on.)

You have also the possibility to sort the listview-contents after each column.
GlobalTrash sorts after the name always - you may change this temporally when
you select one of the titles with the left mousebutton.
@endnode

@node MainMenues "Menu entries (Mainwindow)"
                          @{b}The menus of the main window@{ub}
                         ==============================


GlobalTrash offers the following menu entries in the @{" mainwindow " link MainWindow}:

  - Menu @{b}Project@{ub}:

    - @{u}Preferences...:@{uu} Open the @{" Preferenceswindow " link PrefWindow}.
    - @{u}About...:@{uu}       Open an information requester.
    - @{u}Hide:@{uu}           Close the main window.
    - @{u}Quit:@{uu}           Quit the program.

  - Menu @{b}Edit@{ub}:

    - @{u}Update:@{uu}         Update the contents of the current trashcan directory.
                      If the 'Global'-trashcan is active then the program will
                      update the trashcan directories on all volumes known
                      to GlobalTrash (see @{b}current trashcan@{ub}-Gadget).
    - @{u}Update devices:@{uu} Update the devicelist (e.g., if you create a trashcan
                      directory on a mounted volume).
    - @{u}Select all:@{uu}     Select all files in the listview.
    - @{u}Deselect all:@{uu}   Clear all selections in the listview.
    - @{u}Toggle:@{uu}         Toggle all selections in the listview.
    - @{u}Calculate size:@{uu} Scans the selected directories recursively and calculates
                      the size of the contents; at the same time it refreshes
                      the size of given files.
    - @{u}Register...:@{uu}    Open the @{" registerwindow " link RegisterWindow}.
@endnode

@node PrefWindow "Preferences"
                                 @{b}Preferences@{ub}
                                =============


You can configure GlobalTrash in order to suit your personal needs.
Thus there are, apart from the @{" menu entries " link PrefMenues}, the following options:


  - @{b}General@{ub}:

    - @{u}Command (double-click)@{uu} Define the @{" command " link MainWindow 53} which should be performed
                             if an entry in the listview is double-clicked.
    - @{u}WB-Icon name:@{uu}          Define the name of the appicon which appears on
                             the workbench below the icon (its name) - an empty
                             entry disables the appicon.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 'GlobalTrash'.
    - @{u}WB-Menu name:@{uu}          Define the name of the menu entry in the tools-
                             menu of the workbench - an empty entry disables
                             the menu entry.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 'GlobalTrash' (creates entry).
    - @{u}Default action:@{uu}        Define an AmigaDOS-program which is started
                             every time you drop a volume icon on the appicon
                             (can be used for ejecting ZIP-Discs or to format
                             this volume - if you like that.)
                             This function is used if there isn't any device
                             action defined for this volume (e.g., one without
                             a trashcan-directory).
                             A detailed description of the valid options can
                             be found on the @{" 'device action' " link PrefWindow 84}.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} no command (empty entry).
    - @{u}Default expiration:@{uu}    Define the expiration time for all trashcan-
                             directories which are not already processed by
                             GlobalTrash (e.g., new volumes).
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 7 days.

  - @{b}Interface@{ub}:

    - @{u}Extra space:@{uu}           Define an extra space in pixels between each entry
                             in the listview-gadget.
                             A value of '0' means that GlobalTrash will adapt
                             this value automatically to fit the nearest Image
                             (plus one extra pixel) it can reach (max. 4
                             pixels.)
                             With this value you can set the size of the used
                             file images. These images are present in the sizes
                             10,13 and 16 point. So you can use the 16-point
                             height image by setting this value to
                             16 - <fontheight> (means e.g., '8' Pixel for an 8
                             point topaz.font) and by setting this value to
                             '7' the 13-point images will be used for the
                             same font.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 0 Pixel (automatic).
    - @{u}Font:@{uu}                  Choose the font for the windows.
                             No entry means to use the font of the default
                             public screen.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} empty (default-font).
    - @{u}Filetype-images:@{uu}       Define a file containing the loadable filetype
                             images which are displayed in front of each file
                             or directory. @{b}This option will be selectable with
                             version 1.4 of GlobalTrash!@{ub}
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} empty (default-images).
    - @{u}Icon (empty):@{uu}          Choose the icon file which is used as appicon
                             for GlobalTrash if all trashcan directories
                             (meaning the Global-trashcan) are empty.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 'ENV:sys/def_Trashcan'.
    - @{u}Icon (full):@{uu}           Choose the icon file which is used as appicon
                             for GlobalTrash if there is at least one entry in
                             one trashcan directory on one volume (meaning at
                             least one file in the Global-trashcan.)
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} 'ENV:sys/def_TrashcanFull'.
    - @{u}Get:@{uu}                   Open an ASL-Requester in which you can choose
                             the file(s) you want to get.
    - @{u}Snapshot...:@{uu}           Should be used to snapshot the current position of
                             the appicon on the workbench. A window will be
                             opened and you can choose the desired position by
                             positioning this window. Choosing this gadget again
                             will close the window (or leaving the preferences.)
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} no icon-position.

  - @{b}Volumes@{ub}:

    - @{u}Trashcan:@{uu}              Choose the associated volume for the next two
                             gadgets.
    - @{u}Device action:@{uu}         Define an AmigaDOS-program which is started
                             ervery time you drop the volume icon on the appicon
                             (can be used for ejecting ZIP-Discs or to format
                             this volume - if you like that.)
                             If you want your trashcan-directory emptied if
                             you drop a device icon over the appicon, then you
                             have to define:
                               @{b}'C:Delete <>NIL: ?:Trashcan/~(GlobalTrash.index)'@{ub}
                                 (Replace the '?' with the devicename or the
                                 volumename - 'DH0:' or 'Work' for example).
                               @{b}NOTE: you @{u}MUST NOT@{uu} delete the indexfile
                                     'GlobalTrash.index' !!!@{ub}
                             GlobalTrash supports the following wildcards:
                               - @{b}'%d'@{ub}: Name of the device (e.g., 'DH0:').
                               - @{b}'%p'@{ub}: Name of the frontmost public screen.
                               - @{b}'%v'@{ub}: Name of the volume (e.g., 'Work:').
                             The wildcards will be replaced automatically
                             before invoking the command!
                             Example:
                               'MultiView PUBSCREEN=%p'
                               'EJECT %d'
                             It is possibly to deactivate entries (for a
                             temporally deactivation of the command). Just
                             put a ';' as first character for this. Example:
                               ';EJECT %d'
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} no command (empty entry).
    - @{u}Expiration:@{uu}            Define the expiration time. After this time (in
                             days) all files older than this amount will be
                             automatically deleted.
                             A value of '0' deactivates the automatic-delete
                             for this volume.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} @{b}Default expiration@{ub}.

  - @{b}Miscellaneous@{ub}:

    - @{u}Confirm ...:@{uu}           Turn on the @{b}Delete@{ub} and @{b}Protection@{ub}-requesters.
                             By clearing these flags, GlobalTrash will delete
                             or restore files immediately without asking first
                             (this is also valid for protected files). You can
                             set different values for the following parts:
                               - Start: for the automatically deletion of
                                        expired files (mainly when the program
                                        starts, such as at boot-up.)
                               - GUI:   all delete- or restore operations per-
                                        formed out of the main window.
                               - WB:    all delete- or move operations
                                        performed out of the appicon/menu.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} on (ask).
    - @{u}Save file tree:@{uu}        Defines wheter GlobalTrash should remember the
                             directory-structure. By setting this flag,
                             GlobalTrash will save the contents of the unfolded
                             directories so that these directories are unfolded
                             if you start this program again. Without this
                             flag, GlobalTrash will only save the trashcan-dir-
                             ectory itself - each unfolded directory is folded
                             after starting again.
                             @{b}Default:@{ub} off.

  - @{b}Standard-gadgets@{ub}:

    - @{u}Save:@{uu}                  Save the settings as default (in 'ENVARC:').
                             This settings will also be used for the next
                             start after rebooting.
    - @{u}Use:@{uu}                   Use this settings for now (not saved.)
    - @{u}Cancel:@{uu}                Forget this settings and do not change
                             the current settings (before running the
                             preferences.)
@endnode

@node PrefMenues "Menu entries (preferences window)"
                    @{b}The menu of the preferences window@{ub}
                   ====================================


GlobalTrash offers the following menu entries in its @{" preferences window " link PrefWindow}:

    - Menu @{b}Project@{ub}:

      - @{u}Load...:@{uu}           Load a GlobalTrash-preferences file.
      - @{u}Save (default):@{uu}    Save the preferences as default and close the
                           preferences window (like the @{b}Save@{ub}-gadget.) The
                           saved preferences will be activated again at the
                           next startup.
      - @{u}Save as...:@{uu}        Save a GlobalTrash-preferences file.
                           You can set the path and filename.
      - @{u}Register...:@{uu}       Open the @{" register window " link RegisterWindow}.
      - @{u}About...:@{uu}          Open an information requester.
      - @{u}Quit:@{uu}              Quit the preferences-editor and not save your settings
                           (like the @{b}Cancel@{ub}-gadget).
                           The program itself won't quit.


    - Menu @{b}Edit@{ub}:

      - @{u}Reset to defaults:@{uu} Reset the settings to the default (build-in)
                           settings. You need to activate them with the
                           @{b}Save@{ub}- or @{b}Use@{ub}-gadget.
      - @{u}Last saved:@{uu}        Reset the settings to the last saved (default)
                           settings. Like above, you need to activate them.
      - @{u}Restore:@{uu}           Reset your changes (restore the current settings).
@endnode

@node ProgressBar "Progress-bar"
                               @{b}The progress-bar@{ub}
                              ==================


The progress-bar will be displayed at nearly every operation of GlobalTrash.
It shows which file is currently processed, how many files are already processed
and how many files will be processed totally.

This window will be the only chance to cancel an operation if you disabled the
@{b}Delete@{ub}- and @{b}Protection@{ub}-requester (by selecting the referred @{b}'All'@{ub} option or
by disabling the @{b}Confirm action...@{ub}-gadget in the preferences).
In this window you can select a @{b}Cancel@{ub}-gadget which will cancel the current
action directly after processing the current file.

After finishing the action (all files are processed or the user has aborted)
this window will close automatically.
@endnode

@node Requester "Requester"
                                 @{b}The Requester@{ub}
                                ===============


For security-reasons GlobalTrash will ask the user before performing an
important action (such as delete).
It uses the following requester:

  - @{b}Delete-requester@{ub}:

    Every time an user want to delete a file (and the @{b}Confirm action...@{ub}-option
    is set), the user will be asked if this file should be deleted really.
    GlobalTrash offers you this options:

      - @{u}Delete:@{uu}          Delete the file mentioned in this requester. If there
                         will be more files to process then this requester will
                         appear again for the next file to be deleted.
      - @{u}Delete all:@{uu}      Delete the file mentioned in this requester and all
                         further files without asking again.
      - @{u}Skip:@{uu}            Skip the file mentioned in this requester. If there
                         will be more files to process then this requester will
                         appear again for the next file to be deleted.
      - @{u}Cancel:@{uu}          Cancel the whole operation and don't delete this and
                         any additional files.

      If there is no Trashcan-directory existing on this volume, another
      option will be available:

      - @{u}Create trashcan:@{uu} Create a Trashcan-directory on this volume (without
                         icon) and move the file into it.

  - @{b}Protection-requester@{ub}:

    It can happen that a file to be deleted is protected against deletion.
    In such a case (and the @{b}Confirm action...@{ub}-option is set), this requester
    will appear instead of the @{b}Delete@{ub}-requester (even if you selected the
    @{b}Delete all@{ub}-option of the @{b}Delete@{ub}-requester).
    You will have the following options:

      - @{u}Unprotect:@{uu}       Remove the protection and delete this file. If there
                         will be more files to process, then this requester will
                         appear again for the next file to be deleted and is
                         protected.
      - @{u}All:@{uu}             Remove the protection for this and all further files
                         without asking again. It also deletes these files.
      - @{u}Skip:@{uu}            Don't change the protection-status and skip this
                         file. If there will be more files to be deleted and
                         are protected then this requester will appear again.
      - @{u}Cancel:@{uu}          Cancel the whole operation, don't change the protection-
                         status and don't delete this and any additional files.

      If there is no Trashcan-directory exisiting on this volume, another
      option will be available:

      - @{u}Create trashcan:@{uu} Create a Trashcan-directory on this volume (without
                         icon) and move the file into it (this will not change
                         the protection-status.)

  - @{b}Undelete-requester@{ub}:

    If you want to undelete a file (from which the origin is known), you can
    perform the @{b}Undelete@{ub}-action (otherwise the @{b}Undelete As@{ub}-action will be used.)
    In this case (and the @{b}Confirm action.../GUI@{ub}-option is set), a requester
    with following option will appear:

    - @{u}Undelete:@{uu}     Undelete the file mentioned in this requester at its
                    origin. If the path isn't existent, it will be automatically
                    created. If there are more files to be undeleted then this
                    requester will appear again for the next file.
    - @{u}Undelete all:@{uu} Undelete all selected files at their origin without
                    asking again.
    - @{u}Skip:@{uu}         Skip the mentioned file and ask again if there are
                    more files to be undeleted.
    - @{u}Cancel:@{uu}       Cancel the operation and don't undelete this and any
                    additional files.

    If you undelete a file and a file with this name is already present in
    the path, then another requester with these options will appear:

    - @{u}Overwrite:@{uu}    Overwrite the file mentioned in this requester.
    - @{u}Rename:@{uu}       Open an ASL-Requester in which you can change the path and
                    filename in order to rename the file to be undeleted (like
                    @{b}Undelete as@{ub}).
    - @{u}Duplicate:@{uu}    Change the filename. To do this, GlobalTrash adds an
                    '.dup<X>' (<X> stand for a number) to the filename.
                    For example: if you undelete a file 'Test' and the files
                    'Test', 'Test.dup' and 'Test.dup1' are already in this path,
                    the file will be renamed as 'Test.dup2'.
    - @{u}Skip:@{uu}         Skip the current file and process the next one (if there
                    are any further files.)
    - @{u}Cancel:@{uu}       Cancel the whole operation.

  - @{b}Requester for expired files@{ub}:

    One of the superior features of GlobalTrash is the automatic deletion of
    expired files.
    But before deleting these files (and if the @{b}Confirm action.../Start@{ub} -option is
    set), GlobalTrash will tell the user that there are expired files in the
    trashcan. The user will have the following options:

    - @{u}All:@{uu}    Delete all files without asking any more (and without asking
              about protection-flags.)
    - @{u}Ask:@{uu}    Open the @{b}Delete-@{ub} or @{b}Protection@{ub}-requester for the first file
              (the other files depend on the selection of the new requester.)
    - @{u}Cancel:@{uu} Cancel the current operation and don't delete the expired files.
              The files will be marked as non-expired and they will be expired
              again on the following day.

  - @{b}Requester to emtpy the current trashcan@{ub}:

    If the user selects the @{b}Empty this trash@{ub}-gadget (and the @{b}Confirm
    action.../GUI@{ub}-option is set) a new requester will appear before deleting the
    contents of the current trashcan. The user can choose between following:

    - @{u}Yes:@{uu} Delete the contents of the current trashcan without asking
           again.
    - @{u}No:@{uu}  Cancel the operation without deleting anything.
@endnode

@node RegisterWindow "Register window"
                              @{b}The register window@{ub}
                             =====================


The @{b}User@{ub} gadget is used to enter your registration name and the
@{b}Codenumber@{ub} gadget is used to enter your code number. The required values for these
gadgets are returned by the @{" author " link Author} after you have @{" registered " link Register}.

If both entries are correct, then the @{b}Register@{ub} gadget will be selectable
and you will register by selecting it (you should do so!)

Selecting the @{b}Cancel@{ub} gadget will cancel the whole operation and you won't be
registered (your expiring time allotment will go on...)

If you have to register because you are using this program more than @{b}30 days@{ub},
then the @{b}Cancel@{ub}-gadget will be selectable immediately for another 7 days (37 days
are the maximum time) and then this gadget will be unselectable for a specific
amount of time (about 1/2 second per expired day) - the window must be stay
activated for this time!
@endnode

@node Tooltypes "Tooltypes"     
                                @{b}The tooltypes@{ub}
                               ===============

GlobalTrash knows the following tooltypes:

  - @{u}Commodity tooltypes:@{uu}
    - @{b}CX_POPUP=<YES|NO>:@{ub}       If set to 'YES' the @{" mainwindow " link MainWindow} should open
                               at program-startup.
                               @{u}Default:@{uu} 'NO'.
    - @{b}CX_PRIORITY=<PRI>:@{ub}       Set the Commodity-priority.
                               @{u}Default:@{uu} '0'.
    - @{b}CX_POPKEY=alt g@{ub}          Set the key for opening the mainwindow (pop up).
                               @{u}Default:@{uu} 'alt g'.

  - @{u}GlobalTrash-specific tooltypes:@{uu}
    - @{b}PREFERENCES=<PREFSPATH>:@{ub} Set the path for the preferences-program.
                               This is absolutely necessary, if you want to
                               have access to the @{b}Preferences...@{ub}- or
                               @{b}Register...@{ub}-menu entry and you placed the
                               preferences-program at a location other than
                               the default one!
                               @{u}Default:@{uu} 'SYS:Prefs/GlobalTrashPrefs'.
@endnode

