@node Updates "Updates"
                                @{b}How to update@{ub}
                               ===============


The update-process is very simple. Updates will be made available within the
aminet (you can get the newest version online or on the aminet-cd-roms - but
the version on the cd-rom don't have to be the latest one).

Alternatively you can visit the official support-pages on

    @{b}http://home.pages.de/~bolli/_GlobalTrash/indexe.html@{ub}

or maybe for a german startpoint you may select

    @{b}http://home.pages.de/~bolli/_GlobalTrash/index.html@{ub}

You can get the latest release version and also the latest public-beta versions
from the support-pages.

For all those who haven't internet-access and don't get aminet cd-roms I offer
one more option:
   Send me a letter telling me that you want to have the newest version,
   mention whether you have a 'High-density' (HD) disk-drive and transmit
   me DM 5,- for the disc, shipping and the copy-expense.
   How to transmit the money and what you have to take care about it (no
   coins within an envelope, @{" author-address " link Author}, bank-account, ...) is mentioned
   in the @{" Register " link Register}-section.
@endnode

@node Client "GlobalTrashClient"
                               @{b}GlobalTrashClient@{ub}
                              ===================


GlobalTrashClient is a CLI-/Shell-Interface, which you can use to control
GlobalTrash. Therefore you have these options:

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient <file> [<file> ...]@{ub}'
         Process the given files (the same as dropping them onto the appicon.)
         The action will start immediately (see 'PERFORM').
         @{u}ATTENTION:@{uu} unlike the way of processing files by GlobalTrash you
                    will have to define a file AND its iconfile - otherwise
                    only the file will be processed and the icon is still
                    untouched! So you need to call
                         '@{b}GlobalTrashClient test test.info@{ub}'
                    to delete the file 'test' with its icon!
                    The same is valid for the 'WAIT' and 'PERFORM'-commands.

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient WAIT <file> [<file> ...]@{ub}'
         Process the given files, but does not start immediately. Running the
         Client with the 'PERFORM'-option later on will start the processing
         of all remembered files (or running the Client with another option
         than 'WAIT' or performing an action with GlobalTrash itself like
         opening the main window, dropping a file onto the appicon, etc.)

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient PERFORM [<file> ...]@{ub}'
         Process all previously remembered files (including the files given.)
         This is used to prevent starting the process-action multiple times
         if too many files were given (limitation of AmigaDOS) so that the
         progress-bar or the requesters appear only once and not with every
         command.

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient EMPTY <volume> [<volume> ...]@{ub}'
         Empty the Trashcan-directory on the given volume.
         You will be asked before performing this action.

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient NOASKEMPTY <volume> [<volume> ...]@{ub}'
         Empty the Trashcan-directory on the given volume.
         You @{b}won't@{ub} be asked before performing this action!

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient EMPTYGLOBAL@{ub}'
         Empty the global trashcan - the contents of all trashcan-directories
         on all currently known devices.
         You will be asked before performing this action.

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient NOASKEMPTYGLOBAL@{ub}'
         Empty the global trashcan - the contents of all trashcan-directories
         on all currently known devices.
         You @{b}won't@{ub} be asked before performing this action!

  - '@{b}GlobalTrashClient [OPENGUI]@{ub}'
         Open the main window of GlobalTrash.

@{b}Please note that there are no wildcards supported with this version!@{ub}

With the options you can easily force programs like DirectoryOpus or
ToolManager to use GlobalTrash.

For forcing DirectoryOpus to use GlobalTrash for deleting, you should
configure DirectoryOpus as follows (the lister-toolbar or popup-menus,
for example):

  You define an AmigaDOS-command (or a workbench-command):

    @{b}GlobalTrashClient WAIT {F}@{ub}
    @{b}GlobalTrashClient PERFORM@{ub}

  and the options, you want to use ('Rescan Source' for example.)

Using the other options or using GlobalTrash from other programs is
similar and should be no problem...

Most assuredly you can start the Client from the Shell (per hand).
@endnode

@node Register "How to register"
                               @{b}How to register@{ub}
                              =================


Because I have invested a lot of time and work to get GlobalTrash work, I would
like to have at least a feedback of the users.

I wasn't lucky in declaring my projects as eMail-ware until now. The result is
that this software must be @{b}registered for free@{ub}.
The only feedback (e.g., for my program 'PiccoloSD64Test') I received were
problems and questions by nearly 5 people but nearly every owner of a
PiccoloSD64 used this program. You can receive this program from official
FTP-servers (like the one of Phase5) and you can find it on different
WWW-pages (like the official cybergfx-page) but I never received any kind
of eMail or something else from these people...

@{b}You can use this program without any restrictions and it is fully functional.@{ub}
After an expiration time of 30 days you will be requested to enter your
registration-name and -code (you can avoid this by registering before.)
If you are requested to register and you don't have the name and number, then
you can cancel the registeration (by selecting the @{b}Cancel@{ub}-gadget) and you can use
the program without any further restrictions (except you quit and start again.)


@{u}How can I register ?@{uu}

  There are two options:

  - @{b}eMail:@{ub} - Edit the textfile @{" Register.txt " link Register.txt/main} and send it to the author.
           - nothing more.

  - @{b}Mail:@{ub}  - Edit the textfile @{" Register.txt " link Register.txt/main} and print it out or print it
             first and edit it by hand.
           - Put this page into an envelope and send this letter to the author.
             IMPORTANT: - do not forget to add a sufficiently prepaid and
                          addressed (to you of course; e.g., a SASE) envelope;
                          I won't pay anything to send this letter back to you
                          (because I don't expect any charge!)
                        - if you send a stamp, make sure this is a @{b}german stamp@{ub}.
                        - if you can't get a german stamp, include a @{b}comparable
                          amount of money@{ub} instead (at the moment DM 1,10).
                          Add also the @{b}exchange costs@{ub} if you send foreign money!
                        - @{b}DO NOT SEND ANY COINS!@{ub}
           - Be patient if you didn't receive this answer within one week.
             eMail should be faster of course!

  @{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub} I won't accept incomplete registration-forms anymore.
             All parts of the registration-form must be submitted  - and
             completely filled out (you can leave out the optional fields!)

             I don't think that this will cost you so much time - if too many
             register with incomplete forms (which means much extra
             work for me), I will consider changing the status of this
             program to shareware, for which you will have to pay - it
             depends on you...

After a (hopefully) short time, you will receive your register name and code
so you are now able to @{" register " link RegisterWindow}.

Independent of both options, I would be glad if I receive a little gift - if
you like and can use this program, you will be invited to send a little gift
with your registration (something you like; e.g., a bar of chocolate, a
registered version of your own program or money) - I will be glad about
everything ;-)
If you add a gift with your registration, you should register per mail
(except if you are sending files) or send this gift later via mail.
If you want to spend money, you can include it in the mail you send or you can
transfer it to the following bank-account:

    Name             : Oliver Blumert
    Institute        : Sparkasse Gross-Gerau (germany)
    Institute-number : 508 525 53
    Account-number   : 143834

Please mention your name and eMail-adress or postal-address!
@endnode

